      • dimOrder

        public KerasModelBuilder dimOrder(KerasLayer.DimOrder dimOrder)
        Manually set dim order for Keras model, i.e. either TENSORFLOW (channels last) or THEANO (channels first). Dim ordering will be automatically inferred from your model file, so don't tamper with this option unless you're sure what you're doing. Explicitly setting dim ordering can be useful for very old Keras models (before version 1.2), for which inference can be difficult.
        Parameters:
        dimOrder - Ordering of dimensions (channels first vs. last)
        Returns:
        Model builder
